Former Kibwezi MP Kalembe Ndile.  Members of Wiper Democratic Party in the United Kingdom have sent a message of condolences to the family and friends of the former member of Parliament Kalembe Ndile following his untimely death that occurred last week.  A statement signed by the Chairman Wiper UK Patrick Kiilu eulogised Kalembe as the man of the people, a true activist for the rights of the ordinary mwananchi and a fearless and devoted Wiper Party supporter.  Mr Kiilu said, “Hon Kalembe was ingeniously easy going with a rare talent of connecting with people from all walks of life. He will be greatly missed”.  The Wiper-UK Secretary General Thomas Musau said Kalembe’s demise was untimely and unfortunate.  Kalembe’s heart was in the village where he was loved  Kalembe Ndile’s heart was in the village where he was loved  Kalembe Ndile: Self-made leader who defended the underprivileged  President Uhuru mourns former MP Kalembe Ndile “Kalembe was a key pillar of the emerging unity of the Kamba community and eastern bloc politics. The political equation has been done a big blow to the Wiper party and the region as whole,” he said.  Ndile, Former Kibwezi MP died at Nairobi Hospital after a long illness.  His younger brother Sam Ndile said the former vocal legislator was taken ill several nights before his death after complaining of stomach pains.  The brother confirmed that Ndile had been in and out of various hospitals for some time before his demise.  Kalembe’s burial will be held on Tuesday at his family home in Mbui Nzau, Kibwezi.   Julius Court, UK Deputy High Commissioner to Kenya talks on the Global Education Summit  UHURU IN GERMANY; President Uhuru Kenyatta wants AMISON elevated to UN  UHURU IN GERMANY; President Uhuru Kenyatta wants AMISON elevated to UN By Mireri Junior | 8 hours ago By Stephen Nzioka | 22 hours ago By Peterson Githaiga | 1 day ago By Philip Muasya | 2 days ago Teacher’s 35-hour ordeal with kidnappers on Eldoret highway